      "writtenOn": "2017-12-08T07:55:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i think this type causes complexity throughout this file:\n\n1) DatacentersTable.datacenters could be just map[int]*config.DatacenterConfig. Then L55-57 is one line `dc :- \u0026config.DatacenterConfig{}`. L153-162 would not be needed because we can do simply `delete d.datacenters[id]` (assuming removals is ids, not ints)\n2) same for DatacentersTable.updates. It would simplify L79-81 to one line `d.updates[id] \u003d dc`\n\nthis type is not needed if we use map[int]*config.DatacenterConfig in DatacentersTable.datacenters and DatacentersTable.updates. having one-per-table type less is simpler. L78-81 would become just `d.updates[id] \u003d dc`\n\nsame in racks.go",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 28,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 32,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "25d04572234dd3648bb1438f0754e6791298ca80",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
